1
00:00:14,890 --> 00:00:16,976
[cheering]

2
00:00:28,279 --> 00:00:31,115
[cheering and applause]

3
00:00:44,211 --> 00:00:47,047
[upbeat drumming]

4
00:00:57,266 --> 00:01:00,144
[cheering and applause
continues]

5
00:01:07,568 --> 00:01:10,654
[♪ "MOUNTAINS"]

6
00:01:13,365 --> 00:01:16,035
[upbeat drumming continues]

7
00:01:18,829 --> 00:01:22,082
[guitar intro]

8
00:01:30,341 --> 00:01:33,052
[guitar intro continues]

9
00:01:50,820 --> 00:01:52,111
[music pauses]

10
00:01:52,112 --> 00:01:54,782
[cheering and applause]

11
00:02:13,384 --> 00:02:16,262
[cheering and applause]

12
00:02:23,394 --> 00:02:26,355
[♪ "MOUNTAINS" resumes]

13
00:02:40,995 --> 00:02:43,122
Are you ready?

14
00:02:47,167 --> 00:02:48,127
What's up? What's up?

15
00:05:44,219 --> 00:05:46,888
[cheering and applause]

16
00:05:46,889 --> 00:05:50,517
[♪ "Thunderous"]

17
00:08:48,362 --> 00:08:49,738
[cheering and applause]

18
00:08:51,907 --> 00:08:55,493
I have a question. Have you been
to one of our concerts?

19
00:08:55,494 --> 00:08:57,036
Ready!

20
00:08:57,037 --> 00:08:59,790
[♪ "Chk Chk Boom"]

21
00:09:10,926 --> 00:09:14,971
Dominating places that we
haven't been to with our music

22
00:09:14,972 --> 00:09:16,180
sounds pretty fun, no?

23
00:09:16,181 --> 00:09:17,349
[laughs]

24
00:09:19,643 --> 00:09:21,227
[whispering voice] Stray Kids.

25
00:09:21,228 --> 00:09:24,523
- [alarm rings]
- Good morning.

26
00:09:26,149 --> 00:09:27,192
Hee!

27
00:09:30,445 --> 00:09:35,408
[in Korean] Well,
it's our first stadium tour.

28
00:09:35,409 --> 00:09:39,830
It's just, how you say it,
the scale has grown so much.

29
00:09:42,958 --> 00:09:46,627
It hasn't been an easy journey.

30
00:09:46,628 --> 00:09:48,212
How can we create a concert

31
00:09:48,213 --> 00:09:50,673
that feels new and fresh
for the fans?

32
00:09:50,674 --> 00:09:53,551
That was our biggest concern.

33
00:09:53,552 --> 00:09:56,220
The part
we focused most on was:

34
00:09:56,221 --> 00:09:59,640
can we really showcase the
true strength of Stray Kids?

35
00:09:59,641 --> 00:10:00,850
Lee Know:
First and foremost was

36
00:10:00,851 --> 00:10:02,810
whether STAY
will enjoy the show.

37
00:10:02,811 --> 00:10:05,104
We kept adjusting things
as the tour went on.

38
00:10:05,105 --> 00:10:10,402
We always want to show
the best version of ourselves.

39
00:10:13,613 --> 00:10:16,324
Man [in English]:
One, two, three, four.

40
00:10:16,325 --> 00:10:18,201
[upbeat music playing]

41
00:10:21,121 --> 00:10:22,788
Changbin [in Korean]:
We wanted to enjoy the stage

42
00:10:22,789 --> 00:10:24,749
like real rock stars,

43
00:10:24,750 --> 00:10:30,588
and if that energy and synergy
could travel through the music,

44
00:10:30,589 --> 00:10:32,590
then even the fans
sitting far away,

45
00:10:32,591 --> 00:10:39,055
who can barely see us, like
the size of a fingernail,

46
00:10:39,056 --> 00:10:40,973
would still be able
to feel it.

47
00:10:40,974 --> 00:10:42,893
That's what
we really focused on.

48
00:10:49,066 --> 00:10:52,735
Seungmin:
The coolness of the outdoor air

49
00:10:52,736 --> 00:10:54,862
and the heat of the crowd

50
00:10:54,863 --> 00:10:58,657
created such
an unforgettable atmosphere.

51
00:10:58,658 --> 00:11:02,203
It makes this tour
feel even more special,

52
00:11:02,204 --> 00:11:07,500
especially since we're visiting
so many new countries.

53
00:11:07,501 --> 00:11:09,293
[in English]
Meeting so many STAYs,

54
00:11:09,294 --> 00:11:13,172
in so many countries,
states, cities,

55
00:11:13,173 --> 00:11:15,841
I'm just very grateful,
because they're the fans

56
00:11:15,842 --> 00:11:19,470
who truly support us from afar.

57
00:11:19,471 --> 00:11:21,389
Hyunjin [in Korean]:
It feels like we're living

58
00:11:21,390 --> 00:11:23,682
the exact days
we used to dream about.

59
00:11:23,683 --> 00:11:27,019
[cheering]

60
00:11:27,020 --> 00:11:29,356
Whoo-hoo!

61
00:11:31,024 --> 00:11:32,650
[cheering]

62
00:11:32,651 --> 00:11:37,613
Hyunjin: The message
of this tour is clear:

63
00:11:37,614 --> 00:11:39,157
We've made it this far.

64
00:11:40,367 --> 00:11:42,952
It's a strong statement

65
00:11:42,953 --> 00:11:46,581
that Stray Kids are ready
to take over the world.

66
00:11:48,375 --> 00:11:49,917
Bang Chan [in English]:
We're here

67
00:11:49,918 --> 00:11:51,252
to show them
a great performance.

68
00:11:51,253 --> 00:11:53,672
Let's show them
what they really came for.

69
00:11:55,215 --> 00:11:57,551
[cheering and applause]

70
00:11:59,177 --> 00:12:01,680
[♪ "JJAM"]

71
00:12:09,479 --> 00:12:10,689
Yeah! Let's go!

72
00:14:46,136 --> 00:14:48,804
LA, make some noise!

73
00:14:48,805 --> 00:14:50,307
[cheering]

74
00:15:11,745 --> 00:15:14,581
[cheering and applause]

75
00:15:18,752 --> 00:15:21,587
What's up, LA?

76
00:15:21,588 --> 00:15:24,882
[cheering]

77
00:15:24,883 --> 00:15:28,428
- Yes, sir. Yes, sir.
- Yes, sir

78
00:15:30,305 --> 00:15:32,473
How are you guys feeling?
You guys feeling good?

79
00:15:32,474 --> 00:15:36,977
[cheering]

80
00:15:36,978 --> 00:15:38,479
Alrighty. Hello, everyone.
We are...

81
00:15:38,480 --> 00:15:40,773
All: Stray Kids!

82
00:15:40,774 --> 00:15:43,567
- [cheering]
- Whoo!

83
00:15:43,568 --> 00:15:46,904
Um, I think it's been
at least two years

84
00:15:46,905 --> 00:15:48,947
since our last visit here in LA.

85
00:15:48,948 --> 00:15:49,948
Am I right?

86
00:15:49,949 --> 00:15:51,700
- Uh-huh.
- Uh-huh.

87
00:15:51,701 --> 00:15:53,160
- Uh-huh.
- It's around there.

88
00:15:53,161 --> 00:15:55,788
But it's great
to meet you guys once again.

89
00:15:55,789 --> 00:15:58,290
Um, quick question.

90
00:15:58,291 --> 00:16:01,502
Hands up if you have been
to a Stray Kids concert before.

91
00:16:01,503 --> 00:16:03,921
- [cheering]
- Whoo!

92
00:16:03,922 --> 00:16:06,340
That's a lot.
That's a lot of hands.

93
00:16:06,341 --> 00:16:09,718
Hands up
if this is your first time.

94
00:16:09,719 --> 00:16:11,512
- [cheering]
- Oh...

95
00:16:11,513 --> 00:16:13,263
- Whoo!
- Good to see you.

96
00:16:13,264 --> 00:16:14,473
Nice to meet you.

97
00:16:14,474 --> 00:16:16,350
[laughs]

98
00:16:16,351 --> 00:16:19,061
Welcome, welcome.
Everyone is welcome here.

99
00:16:19,062 --> 00:16:21,271
This is like
our own little home.

100
00:16:21,272 --> 00:16:22,856
So do whatever you want.

101
00:16:22,857 --> 00:16:26,568
We don't give... We don't care.

102
00:16:26,569 --> 00:16:29,196
- [laughs]
- 'Cause we don't give a...

103
00:16:29,197 --> 00:16:31,657
- Audience: Fuck!
- Oh, yeah. I love this one.

104
00:16:31,658 --> 00:16:35,244
I love, I love
when you guys say that.

105
00:16:35,245 --> 00:16:36,954
Yes, sir.

106
00:16:36,955 --> 00:16:39,415
Anyway, um,
so we have kick-started off

107
00:16:39,416 --> 00:16:43,335
our third world tour,
and it is called dominATE.

108
00:16:43,336 --> 00:16:45,213
- [cheering]
- dominATE.

109
00:16:46,464 --> 00:16:48,465
There is so many of you,

110
00:16:48,466 --> 00:16:50,092
I don't know
where to put my eyes at.

111
00:16:50,093 --> 00:16:51,427
Hello, everyone over there.

112
00:16:51,428 --> 00:16:53,679
[cheering]

113
00:16:53,680 --> 00:16:55,222
You can see so many
up the ceiling.

114
00:16:55,223 --> 00:16:58,183
- Hello, everyone.
- Hello.

115
00:16:58,184 --> 00:17:01,019
- We see every single one.
- You guys can see us, right?

116
00:17:01,020 --> 00:17:03,021
You guys can see us, right?

117
00:17:03,022 --> 00:17:07,192
I mean, we're pretty big, but...
Yeah. [laughs]

118
00:17:07,193 --> 00:17:08,527
- Yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah.
- We're pretty big.

119
00:17:08,528 --> 00:17:11,113
[cheering]

120
00:17:11,114 --> 00:17:12,531
I don't know.

121
00:17:12,532 --> 00:17:14,491
LA, LA, LA.

122
00:17:14,492 --> 00:17:16,995
[cheering]

123
00:17:19,581 --> 00:17:20,999
One more question.

124
00:17:23,042 --> 00:17:28,714
- Are you ready?
- [cheering]

125
00:17:28,715 --> 00:17:31,592
- "District 9!" Let's go.
- Let's go!

126
00:17:31,593 --> 00:17:32,760
Whoa!

127
00:17:32,761 --> 00:17:35,221
[♪ "District 9"]

128
00:20:07,874 --> 00:20:09,708
LA, make some noise!

129
00:20:09,709 --> 00:20:10,709
[cheering and applause]

130
00:20:10,710 --> 00:20:12,962
["District 9" resumes]

131
00:20:55,004 --> 00:20:57,131
[cheering and applause]

132
00:21:01,469 --> 00:21:05,347
Felix: People get surprised
because the way I look

133
00:21:05,348 --> 00:21:08,225
and the way I sound
is very different.

134
00:21:08,226 --> 00:21:10,602
[deep voice]
♪ Un, deux, trois, run... ♪

135
00:21:10,603 --> 00:21:12,187
♪ Maniac... ♪

136
00:21:12,188 --> 00:21:13,522
It's very spicy.

137
00:21:13,523 --> 00:21:14,857
Oh, my God!

138
00:21:15,775 --> 00:21:16,984
Thank you.

139
00:21:16,985 --> 00:21:20,445
[cheering]

140
00:21:20,446 --> 00:21:22,781
Felix: As much as people
do get surprised,

141
00:21:22,782 --> 00:21:26,285
I'm just glad that I can
just receive their curiosity.

142
00:21:27,704 --> 00:21:29,579
When people hear my voice,

143
00:21:29,580 --> 00:21:32,625
I hope that they can feel
a sense of comfort...

144
00:21:34,502 --> 00:21:41,008
whether it's singing,
rapping, narrating, talking.

145
00:21:41,009 --> 00:21:45,762
I always hope that I can reach
out to the people or to fans.

146
00:21:45,763 --> 00:21:48,932
I just wanna be someone
who can always give

147
00:21:48,933 --> 00:21:51,269
that sense of comfort
to anyone.

148
00:21:54,939 --> 00:21:59,234
Hello. We are now on our way
to the stadium.

149
00:21:59,235 --> 00:22:00,777
[cheering]

150
00:22:00,778 --> 00:22:02,487
And as you can hear,

151
00:22:02,488 --> 00:22:04,282
the STAYs are waiting for us.

152
00:22:05,616 --> 00:22:07,034
Can't wait.

153
00:22:07,035 --> 00:22:09,662
[cheering]

154
00:22:13,166 --> 00:22:14,750
Just kidding.
It's Felix. It's Felix.

155
00:22:14,751 --> 00:22:16,793
We're here to see
the Stray Kids concert.

156
00:22:16,794 --> 00:22:19,297
- This is all for her.
- [cheering]

157
00:22:24,719 --> 00:22:27,554
Felix: There are so many fans
and so many other people

158
00:22:27,555 --> 00:22:31,850
that go through
so much hardship,

159
00:22:31,851 --> 00:22:34,020
and I know they'll go through
so much more than me.

160
00:22:35,480 --> 00:22:38,857
Uh, as I know that,

161
00:22:38,858 --> 00:22:43,111
I try to put everyone else first
instead of myself.

162
00:22:43,112 --> 00:22:46,199
[cheering]

163
00:22:49,619 --> 00:22:52,412
Felix: I think back
when I was like 18.

164
00:22:52,413 --> 00:22:55,791
I left school
to pursue this career.

165
00:22:55,792 --> 00:22:57,626
It was a huge step.

166
00:22:57,627 --> 00:23:01,797
Sacrificed a lot to get up
to this point in life.

167
00:23:01,798 --> 00:23:03,590
There are definitely times
where, you know,

168
00:23:03,591 --> 00:23:07,177
I did feel like
I was losing a sense

169
00:23:07,178 --> 00:23:10,014
of who I am, of who I was.

170
00:23:11,516 --> 00:23:15,018
And it did hit me, you know,

171
00:23:15,019 --> 00:23:16,354
why am I really here?

172
00:23:18,940 --> 00:23:23,652
This journey
that I chose to take on

173
00:23:23,653 --> 00:23:26,321
ever since I was little,

174
00:23:26,322 --> 00:23:28,366
but now that
I've achieved it...

175
00:23:30,368 --> 00:23:32,994
why am I still doing it?

176
00:23:32,995 --> 00:23:35,914
I did so many things
to find that answer.

177
00:23:35,915 --> 00:23:40,086
And I think it was really hard
to... find it.

178
00:23:43,381 --> 00:23:46,675
And I was lost.

179
00:23:46,676 --> 00:23:50,345
Yeah, I was lost for...
for quite some time.

180
00:23:50,346 --> 00:23:53,306
And that's just the dark side
that not many people...

181
00:23:53,307 --> 00:23:55,309
actually, that no one knows.

182
00:24:02,483 --> 00:24:05,403
[♪ "Truman"]

183
00:24:17,039 --> 00:24:19,124
Felix: You have to
help yourself out first

184
00:24:19,125 --> 00:24:20,668
in order to help others, right?

185
00:24:23,296 --> 00:24:25,214
[speak Korean]

186
00:24:28,050 --> 00:24:32,137
Felix [in English]: So, yeah, I
try to be that sense of light.

187
00:24:32,138 --> 00:24:36,349
Even though I'm the most
emotional in the team,

188
00:24:36,350 --> 00:24:40,395
I always remind myself,
in the end,

189
00:24:40,396 --> 00:24:43,773
what is my job,
what is my purpose,

190
00:24:43,774 --> 00:24:45,860
what is my, um, mission?

191
00:24:47,195 --> 00:24:48,987
At a time like this,

192
00:24:48,988 --> 00:24:52,991
people still need to see
that sense of light,

193
00:24:52,992 --> 00:24:57,204
and no matter where there is
so much darkness, you know,

194
00:24:57,205 --> 00:25:00,707
I do the best I can to spark
some light in them, you know,

195
00:25:00,708 --> 00:25:03,210
to be the light
for everyone else.

196
00:25:03,211 --> 00:25:06,214
[cheering]

197
00:25:10,760 --> 00:25:13,970
And people need
to have that, you know,

198
00:25:13,971 --> 00:25:19,893
that sense of, uh, love,
and I do the best I can.

199
00:25:19,894 --> 00:25:23,730
And if they truly love me back,
you know,

200
00:25:23,731 --> 00:25:28,485
they'll understand what it is
that I go through.

201
00:25:28,486 --> 00:25:29,987
All good. Yeah, it was good.

202
00:25:31,822 --> 00:25:33,406
Ooh!

203
00:25:33,407 --> 00:25:36,159
[♪ "Back Door"]

204
00:25:36,160 --> 00:25:37,662
[cheering]

205
00:27:44,330 --> 00:27:46,415
LA, make some noise!

206
00:28:22,660 --> 00:28:26,122
[cheering]

207
00:28:39,510 --> 00:28:43,139
[cheering and applause]

208
00:28:44,974 --> 00:28:48,686
[♪ "Chk Chk Boom"]

209
00:28:59,280 --> 00:29:02,324
[cheering]

210
00:31:45,154 --> 00:31:48,197
[cheering and applause]

211
00:31:48,198 --> 00:31:51,785
[♪ "DOMINO"]

212
00:31:53,746 --> 00:31:55,789
LA, are you ready? Let's go.

213
00:35:18,659 --> 00:35:21,537
[cheering and applause]

214
00:35:24,414 --> 00:35:27,084
[♪ "God's Menu"]

215
00:38:10,163 --> 00:38:12,249
[cheering and applause]

216
00:38:17,713 --> 00:38:21,048
Han [in Korean]: It's hard
to put all my emotions

217
00:38:21,049 --> 00:38:22,466
into one word.

218
00:38:22,467 --> 00:38:25,887
They are overwhelmingly
positive feelings.

219
00:38:29,558 --> 00:38:33,270
[laughing] I still don't
consider myself a famous person.

220
00:38:39,276 --> 00:38:40,901
During my debut,
I never imagined

221
00:38:40,902 --> 00:38:42,653
something like this
would happen.

222
00:38:42,654 --> 00:38:45,656
But it is happening to me
in real life now.

223
00:38:45,657 --> 00:38:47,700
[cheering]

224
00:38:47,701 --> 00:38:50,704
[singing in Korean]

225
00:38:56,752 --> 00:39:02,965
The world is watching...
the world is watching us.

226
00:39:02,966 --> 00:39:06,802
To cover the energy
of ten thousand, thirty, forty,

227
00:39:06,803 --> 00:39:09,889
or fifty thousand people

228
00:39:09,890 --> 00:39:14,685
requires so much more
than just a usual mentality.

229
00:39:14,686 --> 00:39:19,523
So at backstage, where it's
dark and you can't see anyone,

230
00:39:19,524 --> 00:39:27,198
I hype myself up
and tell myself over and over,

231
00:39:27,199 --> 00:39:30,868
"I'm gonna kill it today."

232
00:39:30,869 --> 00:39:38,542
I create a crazy persona
within myself

233
00:39:38,543 --> 00:39:43,340
to bring energy to the stage.

234
00:39:52,390 --> 00:39:57,394
Stray Kids' Han
and the person Han Jisung,

235
00:39:57,395 --> 00:40:00,231
those two personas
should have been separated

236
00:40:00,232 --> 00:40:01,816
from the beginning,

237
00:40:01,817 --> 00:40:03,818
but there was a time
when they weren't.

238
00:40:03,819 --> 00:40:06,654
I've lived without
separating the persona,

239
00:40:06,655 --> 00:40:11,742
which confused me.

240
00:40:11,743 --> 00:40:16,872
I think I was too young with my
ego not being fully developed,

241
00:40:16,873 --> 00:40:21,460
and living this life, there
was a lot of unfamiliarity,

242
00:40:21,461 --> 00:40:24,130
a lot of things that were
scary and frightening.

243
00:40:24,131 --> 00:40:27,675
So, when I had a hard time
handling all these situations,

244
00:40:27,676 --> 00:40:29,802
the members would
sometimes get angry at me.

245
00:40:29,803 --> 00:40:32,596
But they also gave me
real and truthful advice.

246
00:40:32,597 --> 00:40:35,349
I really benefited
from our members.

247
00:40:35,350 --> 00:40:41,898
I found a lot of inner peace,
a boost of inner strength.

248
00:40:44,568 --> 00:40:52,950
I'm the polar opposite
of a perfectionist.

249
00:40:52,951 --> 00:40:57,872
I'm usually the one who makes
a lot of small mistakes,

250
00:40:57,873 --> 00:41:02,126
including
in the choreography.

251
00:41:02,127 --> 00:41:05,171
Whenever I try to be
more perfect

252
00:41:05,172 --> 00:41:08,507
and force myself
not to make mistakes,

253
00:41:08,508 --> 00:41:12,678
everything just gets
erased from my memory.

254
00:41:12,679 --> 00:41:16,849
I have that weird symptom,
so I am not a perfectionist.

255
00:41:16,850 --> 00:41:21,937
I'm just a guy
who really enjoys the moment.

256
00:41:21,938 --> 00:41:27,902
Just being myself
brings such joy.

257
00:41:27,903 --> 00:41:30,779
And I know
it takes a lot of courage

258
00:41:30,780 --> 00:41:32,823
to live the way you want,

259
00:41:32,824 --> 00:41:39,163
and it requires a lot of effort
to live that way.

260
00:41:39,164 --> 00:41:41,749
I think when I was younger,
I had a goal

261
00:41:41,750 --> 00:41:43,918
where I believed I would be
happy and successful

262
00:41:43,919 --> 00:41:47,005
when I reached
a certain point.

263
00:41:49,257 --> 00:41:53,177
But now if I reach
the highest goal

264
00:41:53,178 --> 00:41:56,138
I have set for myself
and maintain that level,

265
00:41:56,139 --> 00:42:02,687
that's when I feel I have
succeeded, not just hit it once.

266
00:42:05,065 --> 00:42:09,068
As for the biggest insecurity,
like the saying,

267
00:42:09,069 --> 00:42:11,404
"You lose something precious
when you become so used to it,"

268
00:42:13,156 --> 00:42:17,451
I would be scared of becoming
used to the spotlight,

269
00:42:17,452 --> 00:42:22,791
this situation,
the cheers, and the love.

270
00:42:29,130 --> 00:42:30,965
Even now,

271
00:42:30,966 --> 00:42:34,719
I feel I'm still living
in my imagination or a dream.

272
00:42:39,641 --> 00:42:42,519
[cheering and applause]

273
00:42:48,066 --> 00:42:50,860
[♪ "Truman"]

274
00:45:46,327 --> 00:45:47,203
[in English] What's up?

275
00:45:49,789 --> 00:45:52,959
[cheering and applause]

276
00:46:00,842 --> 00:46:03,886
[♪ "Burnin' Tires"]

277
00:46:03,887 --> 00:46:05,722
[cheering]

278
00:46:58,358 --> 00:46:59,776
Everybody, sing!

279
00:48:22,525 --> 00:48:26,321
[motorbike engines roar]

280
00:48:40,001 --> 00:48:42,587
[cheering and applause]

281
00:48:44,255 --> 00:48:48,216
[♪ "Burnin' Tires" continues]

282
00:48:48,217 --> 00:48:49,510
Are you guys ready?

283
00:49:30,009 --> 00:49:32,929
[cheering and applause]

284
00:49:38,518 --> 00:49:39,644
Boom!

285
00:49:43,731 --> 00:49:45,400
It's definitely
not working today.

286
00:49:47,694 --> 00:49:50,822
Wake up. Wake up, my baby.

287
00:49:51,364 --> 00:49:52,448
Boom!

288
00:49:54,367 --> 00:49:57,577
Ah! ♪ Boom, boom, boom
Gotta kick it ♪

289
00:49:57,578 --> 00:49:59,746
♪ Boom,
boom, boom, gotta kick it ♪

290
00:49:59,747 --> 00:50:02,624
♪ Boom, boom, boom, gotta kick,
kick, kick, kick, kick, kick ♪

291
00:50:02,625 --> 00:50:05,836
Everybody sing it.
♪ Boom, boom, boom ♪

292
00:50:05,837 --> 00:50:10,006
♪ Boom, boom, boom
Boom, boom, boom ♪

293
00:50:10,007 --> 00:50:11,883
♪ Boom, boom, boom ♪

294
00:50:11,884 --> 00:50:14,886
- It's not working.
- I'll try it.

295
00:50:14,887 --> 00:50:16,013
- Okay, I.N, you try.
- Okay.

296
00:50:18,558 --> 00:50:20,977
[cheering]

297
00:50:24,772 --> 00:50:27,649
Um, what is the problem?

298
00:50:27,650 --> 00:50:31,111
I think we need your help.

299
00:50:31,112 --> 00:50:33,822
- [cheering]
- Will you guys help us?

300
00:50:33,823 --> 00:50:36,199
- [cheering]
- Really?

301
00:50:36,200 --> 00:50:39,578
- [cheering]
- Let's try.

302
00:50:39,579 --> 00:50:43,415
♪ Ba-ra-ba-bam
I'm runnin' until the end ♪

303
00:50:43,416 --> 00:50:45,876
♪ Ba-ra-ba-bam
Get out of my way ♪

304
00:50:45,877 --> 00:50:47,502
- Both: Sing!
- ♪ Ba-ra-ba-bam ♪

305
00:50:47,503 --> 00:50:49,713
♪ I'm runnin' until the end ♪

306
00:50:49,714 --> 00:50:52,174
♪ Ba-ra-ba-bam
Get out of my way ♪

307
00:50:52,175 --> 00:50:57,721
- Ah, not bad, not bad.
- Not yet. Not yet. More louder!

308
00:50:57,722 --> 00:51:00,849
♪ Ba-ra-ba-bam
I'm burnin' until the end ♪

309
00:51:00,850 --> 00:51:03,310
♪ Ba-ra-ba-bam
Get out of my way ♪

310
00:51:03,311 --> 00:51:05,771
- Both: Sing!
- ♪ Ba-ra-ba-bam ♪

311
00:51:05,772 --> 00:51:07,522
♪ I'm burnin' until the end ♪

312
00:51:07,523 --> 00:51:10,358
♪ Ba-ra-ba-bam
Get out of my way ♪

313
00:51:10,359 --> 00:51:12,278
Okay, let's try one more time.

314
00:51:16,741 --> 00:51:18,034
[cheering]

315
00:51:23,289 --> 00:51:25,123
- Choo!
- Bam!

316
00:51:25,124 --> 00:51:27,043
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

317
00:51:28,544 --> 00:51:30,463
[cheering]

318
00:51:41,808 --> 00:51:45,061
[in Korean] Hi. I'm the youngest
member of Stray Kids, I.N.

319
00:51:47,146 --> 00:51:51,025
In Stray Kids, the youngest guy
is the true power.

320
00:51:52,151 --> 00:51:55,403
Maybe they already know?
[laughs]

321
00:51:55,404 --> 00:51:58,199
[♪ "MOUNTAINS"]

322
00:52:03,955 --> 00:52:05,664
I.N: When we first started,

323
00:52:05,665 --> 00:52:09,292
I still remember our very first
performance on TV.

324
00:52:09,293 --> 00:52:11,336
I couldn't find the cameras.

325
00:52:11,337 --> 00:52:13,505
I didn't know what face
I was making,

326
00:52:13,506 --> 00:52:16,299
and I didn't know
how to interact with the fans.

327
00:52:16,300 --> 00:52:20,637
Honestly, I am such
an overthinker. I'm sensitive.

328
00:52:20,638 --> 00:52:22,556
I don't show it often,

329
00:52:22,557 --> 00:52:27,018
but I'm a little sensitive
about small things.

330
00:52:27,019 --> 00:52:32,315
I never show this outside.

331
00:52:32,316 --> 00:52:36,361
I always try to be optimistic.

332
00:52:36,362 --> 00:52:37,863
[cheering]

333
00:52:37,864 --> 00:52:40,740
[in English]
I'm the youngest, I.N. Whoo!

334
00:52:40,741 --> 00:52:45,120
[in Korean] My source of
confidence is my fandom, STAY.

335
00:52:45,121 --> 00:52:50,042
I get a lot of encouragement
from their support.

336
00:52:51,419 --> 00:52:54,838
And the world tour now

337
00:52:54,839 --> 00:52:57,841
is my first time performing
in front of so many people.

338
00:52:57,842 --> 00:53:04,180
This tour
was truly unimaginable.

339
00:53:04,181 --> 00:53:08,269
I am incredibly happy
and proud of it.

340
00:53:10,396 --> 00:53:14,983
It's amazing to see
how fans can sing along,

341
00:53:14,984 --> 00:53:17,402
regardless of language.

342
00:53:17,403 --> 00:53:19,863
I am always moved
when I see them

343
00:53:19,864 --> 00:53:22,157
sing along with us in unison,

344
00:53:22,158 --> 00:53:27,747
as I feel their big love.

345
00:53:30,207 --> 00:53:34,169
I am so thankful
that so many people love us.

346
00:53:34,170 --> 00:53:38,924
I think I've learned
to love myself

347
00:53:38,925 --> 00:53:42,969
the way these fans love me.

348
00:53:42,970 --> 00:53:45,806
[singing in Korean]

349
00:53:55,316 --> 00:54:00,654
I always feel that our members
are truly amazing,

350
00:54:00,655 --> 00:54:07,535
mainly because, despite
their exceptional talent,

351
00:54:07,536 --> 00:54:12,707
they still think
they are not good enough.

352
00:54:12,708 --> 00:54:16,836
They always find ways
to improve.

353
00:54:16,837 --> 00:54:18,964
I learned from them

354
00:54:18,965 --> 00:54:24,136
and motivate myself
to continue improving.

355
00:54:25,805 --> 00:54:32,269
I want to be an artist
loved by the entire world.

356
00:54:34,563 --> 00:54:42,612
Right now, I have so many fans
cheering for me.

357
00:54:42,613 --> 00:54:48,410
Stray Kids' I.N
will always exist,

358
00:54:48,411 --> 00:54:53,373
but will the fandom, STAY,
be with us forever?

359
00:54:53,374 --> 00:54:58,336
That thought scares me.

360
00:54:58,337 --> 00:55:01,549
[cheering]

361
00:55:04,301 --> 00:55:10,473
To be honest, I don't believe
this moment will last forever,

362
00:55:10,474 --> 00:55:16,062
even though I am trying hard
to make it last,

363
00:55:16,063 --> 00:55:20,901
and I will keep trying.

364
00:55:23,612 --> 00:55:29,325
I just want to cherish
the moment of touring,

365
00:55:29,326 --> 00:55:34,290
connecting with fans
through music.

366
00:55:35,416 --> 00:55:37,917
[♪ "ESCAPE"]

367
00:55:37,918 --> 00:55:40,713
[cheering]

368
00:59:07,253 --> 00:59:10,381
[cheering and applause]

369
00:59:15,844 --> 00:59:18,888
[♪ "CINEMA"]

370
00:59:18,889 --> 00:59:21,141
[cheering]

371
00:59:32,152 --> 00:59:34,738
[cheering]

372
01:02:43,260 --> 01:02:47,930
Hey, yo, LA. Look around.
This is your moment.

373
01:02:47,931 --> 01:02:49,974
You showed up.
You brought the fire.

374
01:02:49,975 --> 01:02:52,435
When it's all over,
don't forget,

375
01:02:52,436 --> 01:02:54,687
your name's written
all over this night.

376
01:02:54,688 --> 01:02:57,024
[♪ "CINEMA" resumes]

377
01:03:54,540 --> 01:03:57,209
[cheering and applause]

378
01:04:04,967 --> 01:04:06,551
[in Korean]
Initially, it started

379
01:04:06,552 --> 01:04:08,094
from the pure joy of the craft.

380
01:04:08,095 --> 01:04:10,137
I can only stick with something
if it's fun,

381
01:04:10,138 --> 01:04:12,266
so, for me, enjoying it
is the important part.

382
01:04:13,767 --> 01:04:15,142
During our debut days,

383
01:04:15,143 --> 01:04:17,603
I always felt rushed
and unprepared,

384
01:04:17,604 --> 01:04:21,274
like no matter how much
I practiced, it wasn't enough.

385
01:04:21,275 --> 01:04:24,068
I constantly felt overwhelmed
with anxiety.

386
01:04:24,069 --> 01:04:26,779
I haven't checked
this dance part.

387
01:04:26,780 --> 01:04:29,865
[sings in Korean]

388
01:04:29,866 --> 01:04:32,201
I thought I'd get shy
in front of a big crowd,

389
01:04:32,202 --> 01:04:36,205
but, surprisingly,
the bigger the crowd,

390
01:04:36,206 --> 01:04:39,960
the more confident I felt.

391
01:04:41,962 --> 01:04:44,130
This is our biggest concert
since debut,

392
01:04:44,131 --> 01:04:47,550
and I'm so happy
for the opportunity

393
01:04:47,551 --> 01:04:51,930
to see all the STAY
around the world.

394
01:04:56,143 --> 01:04:58,978
Every country has
its own vibe and energy,

395
01:04:58,979 --> 01:05:02,357
and that uniqueness is what
makes it all so exciting.

396
01:05:08,155 --> 01:05:10,699
Sometimes I wonder, what
makes people like us so much?

397
01:05:17,289 --> 01:05:18,915
It still feels surreal.

398
01:05:21,168 --> 01:05:24,462
Honestly, being famous
is just a label.

399
01:05:24,463 --> 01:05:28,132
When I walk around in Korea,
no one recognizes me.

400
01:05:28,133 --> 01:05:31,969
So I don't really
feel the fame.

401
01:05:31,970 --> 01:05:33,639
I still feel like
the same old me.

402
01:05:34,973 --> 01:05:42,356
[sings in Korean]

403
01:05:48,570 --> 01:05:50,488
[in English] One-man show.

404
01:05:50,489 --> 01:05:51,281
[chuckles]

405
01:05:53,283 --> 01:05:55,201
Lee Know [in Korean]:
I don't think people are moved

406
01:05:55,202 --> 01:05:57,453
just by the sound of my voice,

407
01:05:57,454 --> 01:06:02,500
but rather by the message
of the song I'm singing.

408
01:06:02,501 --> 01:06:05,336
So I always try to voice
the meaning of the song

409
01:06:05,337 --> 01:06:11,092
and hope the message
really connects with the fans.

410
01:06:11,093 --> 01:06:14,261
Is that too "T" (MBTI)
of an answer?

411
01:06:14,262 --> 01:06:16,932
[singing in Korean]

412
01:06:22,187 --> 01:06:24,647
Lee Know:
I really admire my members.

413
01:06:24,648 --> 01:06:26,941
No matter how busy we are,

414
01:06:26,942 --> 01:06:29,151
they're still writing songs
and creating.

415
01:06:29,152 --> 01:06:31,070
So much respect for them.

416
01:06:31,071 --> 01:06:33,739
We've built up so much trust
over the years

417
01:06:33,740 --> 01:06:35,616
that our hearts connect.

418
01:06:35,617 --> 01:06:40,163
We can understand each other
without saying a word.

419
01:06:44,376 --> 01:06:48,629
Whenever things get tough,
I just remind myself

420
01:06:48,630 --> 01:06:52,800
why I started all this
and what has kept me going.

421
01:06:52,801 --> 01:06:55,803
If future K-pop artists
ever say,

422
01:06:55,804 --> 01:06:58,389
"I wanted to become an idol
because of Stray Kids,"

423
01:06:58,390 --> 01:07:02,518
I think that would mean
the world to me.

424
01:07:02,519 --> 01:07:04,019
Just like how I became one

425
01:07:04,020 --> 01:07:05,981
after looking up
to the idols I admired.

426
01:07:06,982 --> 01:07:08,691
[cheering]

427
01:07:08,692 --> 01:07:11,194
[♪ "GIANT"]

428
01:10:47,702 --> 01:10:51,121
[cheering and applause]

429
01:10:51,122 --> 01:10:53,208
[♪ "Walkin On Water"]

430
01:13:48,508 --> 01:13:51,135
[cheering and applause]

431
01:13:51,136 --> 01:13:54,264
[♪ "S-Class"]

432
01:17:27,602 --> 01:17:30,897
[cheering and applause]

433
01:17:34,484 --> 01:17:37,819
[in Korean] There are times
when I get burnt out, of course.

434
01:17:37,820 --> 01:17:40,572
I think I feel it the most

435
01:17:40,573 --> 01:17:43,283
when I am preparing
for the next album.

436
01:17:43,284 --> 01:17:51,208
To make a good album, we need
to come up with good songs.

437
01:17:51,209 --> 01:17:54,044
But when I can't think of
melodic symbols or inspiration,

438
01:17:54,045 --> 01:17:56,004
it's frustrating,
and I feel burnt out,

439
01:17:56,005 --> 01:17:57,964
thinking,
is this my limitation?

440
01:17:57,965 --> 01:18:00,592
Okay, I think it'll sound better
if it sounded a bit fuller.

441
01:18:00,593 --> 01:18:02,386
- Okay.
- Okay.

442
01:18:02,387 --> 01:18:05,055
Stay on beat with the rhythm.
Bam! Bam! Bam! Bam!

443
01:18:05,056 --> 01:18:06,723
- Just stay on the beat.
- Okay.

444
01:18:06,724 --> 01:18:08,850
Changbin:
I think the members and STAY

445
01:18:08,851 --> 01:18:11,228
make me that way.

446
01:18:11,229 --> 01:18:19,694
Being a member of Stray Kids
comes with a responsibility

447
01:18:19,695 --> 01:18:23,073
with the role that I have,
so that gives me the motivation

448
01:18:23,074 --> 01:18:31,081
and makes me become
a more earnest, diligent person.

449
01:18:31,082 --> 01:18:34,042
It would be a lie
if I said there's no pressure.

450
01:18:34,043 --> 01:18:38,672
But I try to enjoy
that pressure as much as I can.

451
01:18:38,673 --> 01:18:42,217
I never want to show
the weak side of me on stage

452
01:18:42,218 --> 01:18:44,136
or in any of our content.

453
01:18:44,137 --> 01:18:47,682
I think it's because I don't
want to see myself break down.

454
01:18:52,728 --> 01:18:55,690
I think I just became
that person.

455
01:18:58,443 --> 01:19:03,196
I was always afraid of
slowing down or falling behind.

456
01:19:03,197 --> 01:19:08,535
I really don't like
that kind of lifestyle.

457
01:19:08,536 --> 01:19:11,830
So I always put pressure
on myself and the members

458
01:19:11,831 --> 01:19:16,042
to just constantly
go forward, do more.

459
01:19:16,043 --> 01:19:20,589
I was definitely
that kind of person.

460
01:19:20,590 --> 01:19:24,134
[in English] Today
my voice condition is very good.

461
01:19:24,135 --> 01:19:27,387
So I will...
I will break your stage.

462
01:19:27,388 --> 01:19:31,475
I practiced so hard.
So, look forward to it.

463
01:19:31,476 --> 01:19:34,645
Let's go, let's go,
let's go, let's go.

464
01:19:37,190 --> 01:19:42,819
[in Korean] But recently...
I started to think

465
01:19:42,820 --> 01:19:45,739
maybe slowing down for a second
is necessary.

466
01:19:45,740 --> 01:19:50,452
On stage, that might keep
Stray Kids more healthy.

467
01:19:50,453 --> 01:19:58,877
I show a dark and powerful,
just strong image overall,

468
01:19:58,878 --> 01:20:01,796
but I'm also one of the members
with brighter energy.

469
01:20:01,797 --> 01:20:06,468
Melbourne show. dominATE.

470
01:20:06,469 --> 01:20:08,011
But, unlike what people think,

471
01:20:08,012 --> 01:20:09,804
when I am alone,
I am really quiet.

472
01:20:09,805 --> 01:20:13,308
I'm actually pretty laid back.

473
01:20:13,309 --> 01:20:15,477
There might be
a sensitive side of myself

474
01:20:15,478 --> 01:20:17,687
that is different from the
strong image that I portray.

475
01:20:17,688 --> 01:20:20,857
And there's also
an emotional part of me,

476
01:20:20,858 --> 01:20:23,235
but I don't see that
as being weak.

477
01:20:23,236 --> 01:20:24,779
[singing in Korean]

478
01:20:29,825 --> 01:20:32,202
I might be shining on stage,

479
01:20:32,203 --> 01:20:35,664
but the person I am
hasn't changed at all.

480
01:20:35,665 --> 01:20:37,415
I'm just same old Changbin.

481
01:20:37,416 --> 01:20:41,795
Stray Kids Changbin
is who I am.

482
01:20:41,796 --> 01:20:47,008
I used to think the only
strength that can move me

483
01:20:47,009 --> 01:20:49,970
was myself
and myself alone,

484
01:20:49,971 --> 01:20:51,680
and that I am the only one

485
01:20:51,681 --> 01:20:53,140
that can handle
the pressure and endure.

486
01:20:55,226 --> 01:21:01,523
But I realized I get strength
from people around me as well.

487
01:21:01,524 --> 01:21:04,985
Last show, Changbin.
Last show. Let's do this.

488
01:21:04,986 --> 01:21:08,196
- [in English] Fighting.
- Fighting.

489
01:21:08,197 --> 01:21:11,157
- Forza. Forza.
- Forza.

490
01:21:11,158 --> 01:21:13,410
Changbin [in Korean]:
I'm thankful for those

491
01:21:13,411 --> 01:21:14,953
who listen to our music,

492
01:21:14,954 --> 01:21:18,081
understand us
and give comfort to us.

493
01:21:18,082 --> 01:21:20,625
I am also thankful
that there are people

494
01:21:20,626 --> 01:21:23,295
who get comfort
through our music.

495
01:21:23,296 --> 01:21:25,881
In front of STAY,
when they hear my voice,

496
01:21:27,925 --> 01:21:29,509
I want them
to feel the resonance,

497
01:21:29,510 --> 01:21:31,845
just like
the emotional feeling I get

498
01:21:31,846 --> 01:21:35,432
when I hear STAY
singing along to our song.

499
01:21:35,433 --> 01:21:38,977
I hope they are moved
by my voice

500
01:21:38,978 --> 01:21:40,521
as much as I'm moved
by theirs.

501
01:21:44,483 --> 01:21:49,362
It makes me think again that
"This is the power of music!"

502
01:21:49,363 --> 01:21:54,659
I think more and more
about the thoughts, emotions

503
01:21:54,660 --> 01:22:00,248
and comfort people would have
when listening to our music.

504
01:22:00,249 --> 01:22:03,294
I always think I have to
show my best every time.

505
01:22:05,921 --> 01:22:09,800
I don't want to let them down.

506
01:22:12,094 --> 01:22:14,596
[♪ "Lonely St."]

507
01:22:14,597 --> 01:22:16,640
[cheering]

508
01:22:16,641 --> 01:22:17,725
Whoo!

509
01:22:34,742 --> 01:22:36,327
[in English] One more time!

510
01:22:37,495 --> 01:22:38,704
Louder.

511
01:23:25,000 --> 01:23:26,419
Put your hands up!

512
01:24:29,273 --> 01:24:31,025
Put your hands in the air.

513
01:24:39,784 --> 01:24:40,659
Everybody.

514
01:24:53,923 --> 01:24:55,840
[cheering and applause]

515
01:24:55,841 --> 01:24:59,053
[♪ "Cover Me"]

516
01:28:02,736 --> 01:28:05,572
[cheering and applause]

517
01:28:22,464 --> 01:28:28,803
♪ So cover me now... ♪

518
01:28:28,804 --> 01:28:30,180
Felix: LA, sing together.

519
01:28:32,599 --> 01:28:39,732
[audience] ♪ Now ♪

520
01:28:41,108 --> 01:28:46,612
♪ Now... ♪

521
01:28:46,613 --> 01:28:48,198
Felix: One more time, together.

522
01:28:49,825 --> 01:28:56,289
[audience] ♪ Now ♪

523
01:28:56,290 --> 01:28:59,208
Whoo! Yes, sir.

524
01:28:59,209 --> 01:29:01,670
[cheering]

525
01:29:08,093 --> 01:29:09,635
[in Korean]
When I am not prepared

526
01:29:09,636 --> 01:29:11,471
or haven't practiced
hard enough,

527
01:29:11,472 --> 01:29:13,806
the stress level of making
a mistake is very high.

528
01:29:13,807 --> 01:29:17,435
So before I leave
for a concert overseas,

529
01:29:17,436 --> 01:29:19,021
I train to be 100% ready.

530
01:29:23,233 --> 01:29:27,987
I am... done
with the group choreo practice.

531
01:29:27,988 --> 01:29:33,493
And now going
straight to my guitar lesson.

532
01:29:33,494 --> 01:29:37,747
There's always pressure,
and I know my role is big.

533
01:29:37,748 --> 01:29:41,417
I try to prepare
through continuous practice

534
01:29:41,418 --> 01:29:43,920
and by believing in myself.

535
01:29:43,921 --> 01:29:46,090
[singing in Korean]

536
01:29:50,219 --> 01:29:54,597
I try to sleep regularly
during the tour.

537
01:29:54,598 --> 01:29:59,477
There is a limit to the human
body, so when I'm tired,

538
01:29:59,478 --> 01:30:03,815
my throat closes up or the
sound doesn't come out right.

539
01:30:03,816 --> 01:30:06,610
[cheering]

540
01:30:09,279 --> 01:30:12,824
I invest a lot in sleep
during the tour

541
01:30:12,825 --> 01:30:15,243
so that I can fully recover
my body and mind

542
01:30:15,244 --> 01:30:17,371
to perform at my best
in front of the audience.

543
01:30:30,134 --> 01:30:32,844
One, two, three!

544
01:30:32,845 --> 01:30:36,223
Okay, we're still in the process
of making our performance.

545
01:30:39,184 --> 01:30:43,813
I thought I wouldn't be able
to recover if I fall apart,

546
01:30:43,814 --> 01:30:47,108
so instead of falling apart
and being down,

547
01:30:47,109 --> 01:30:48,985
I didn't give myself a choice

548
01:30:48,986 --> 01:30:52,196
but forced myself to
practice more or train harder.

549
01:30:52,197 --> 01:30:55,950
I was very anxious
about going up to perform.

550
01:30:55,951 --> 01:30:58,620
Even after rehearsing with the
members, I stayed afterward.

551
01:30:59,913 --> 01:31:02,499
Last VIP sound check.

552
01:31:07,129 --> 01:31:10,214
I'll do my best until the end.

553
01:31:10,215 --> 01:31:13,426
I know this opportunity
is not to be taken for granted

554
01:31:13,427 --> 01:31:15,970
and should be held
with responsibility.

555
01:31:15,971 --> 01:31:18,097
With so many people
coming to our concert,

556
01:31:18,098 --> 01:31:23,603
I want to give every fan
at the concert

557
01:31:23,604 --> 01:31:26,147
satisfaction when they go home.

558
01:31:26,148 --> 01:31:31,361
I tried my best to hold up
my end of the performance.

559
01:31:34,698 --> 01:31:37,117
[cheering]

560
01:31:42,831 --> 01:31:46,250
Performing on a huge stage,
like at an outdoor festival,

561
01:31:46,251 --> 01:31:50,463
with the crowd bouncing to
our music and their hands up,

562
01:31:50,464 --> 01:31:53,132
is the image of a singer
that I have dreamt about.

563
01:31:53,133 --> 01:31:57,720
Throughout our stadium tour,
there were overlapping scenes.

564
01:31:57,721 --> 01:32:01,307
It's so similar
to what I've been dreaming of.

565
01:32:01,308 --> 01:32:03,768
When I'm on stage
with the members,

566
01:32:03,769 --> 01:32:08,439
I realize how happy
and sincere I am

567
01:32:08,440 --> 01:32:12,569
about this job that I have.

568
01:32:17,199 --> 01:32:19,784
Ever since I was young,

569
01:32:19,785 --> 01:32:23,537
I could feel the strength
of music as being powerful,

570
01:32:23,538 --> 01:32:26,457
and its presence must live on.

571
01:32:26,458 --> 01:32:30,002
I want to preserve music

572
01:32:30,003 --> 01:32:33,590
and believe it's my role
to immerse people in it.

573
01:32:35,717 --> 01:32:37,594
[in English] Music is my life.
[laughs]

574
01:32:38,804 --> 01:32:40,680
[cheering]

575
01:32:40,681 --> 01:32:46,520
All right, I think it's time
to warm up again. Uh...

576
01:32:47,813 --> 01:32:49,647
Just gonna check, uh...

577
01:32:49,648 --> 01:32:51,525
LA, can we have
all your hands up?

578
01:32:52,484 --> 01:32:53,693
Okay.

579
01:32:53,694 --> 01:32:56,654
Can we have two hands up?

580
01:32:56,655 --> 01:32:59,490
Okay. Beautiful.

581
01:32:59,491 --> 01:33:02,410
I think we're okay to move on.

582
01:33:02,411 --> 01:33:04,620
Band members, are you ready?

583
01:33:04,621 --> 01:33:06,080
Stray Kids, are you ready?

584
01:33:06,081 --> 01:33:07,832
All: Yes, sir!

585
01:33:07,833 --> 01:33:09,583
STAY, are you ready?

586
01:33:09,584 --> 01:33:11,210
- [cheering]
- Felix: Yes, sir.

587
01:33:11,211 --> 01:33:13,547
- Yes, sir.
- I said...

588
01:33:15,007 --> 01:33:17,508
STAY, are you ready?

589
01:33:17,509 --> 01:33:20,052
[cheering]

590
01:33:20,053 --> 01:33:21,888
'Cause we don't give a...

591
01:33:24,433 --> 01:33:25,683
- Felix: Okay.
- Ow!

592
01:33:25,684 --> 01:33:26,767
Felix: Let's go!

593
01:33:26,768 --> 01:33:29,770
(thunder rumbles)

594
01:33:29,771 --> 01:33:32,482
Hands up, everyone.
Put your hands up!

595
01:33:34,151 --> 01:33:36,778
[♪ "TOPLINE"]

596
01:36:15,645 --> 01:36:17,564
[cheering and applause]

597
01:36:20,525 --> 01:36:22,151
Felix: You ready?

598
01:36:22,152 --> 01:36:24,738
[♪ "Social Path"]

599
01:37:01,483 --> 01:37:02,442
Yeah.

600
01:39:35,261 --> 01:39:38,139
[cheering and applause]

601
01:39:39,891 --> 01:39:41,892
- Yeah, let's go.
- LA, are you ready?

602
01:39:41,893 --> 01:39:44,103
[cheering]

603
01:39:44,104 --> 01:39:45,939
[♪ "LALALALA"]

604
01:39:47,732 --> 01:39:49,692
You ready?

605
01:39:49,693 --> 01:39:51,653
Let's go! Let's go!

606
01:39:55,532 --> 01:39:56,574
Sing it!

607
01:40:45,999 --> 01:40:48,001
Everybody, sing it!

608
01:42:05,995 --> 01:42:07,038
Felix: Sing!

609
01:43:17,817 --> 01:43:20,612
[cheering and applause]

610
01:43:25,033 --> 01:43:27,409
Hyunjin [in Korean]:
When I think of myself,

611
01:43:27,410 --> 01:43:29,202
how I am on stage
is the side of myself

612
01:43:29,203 --> 01:43:31,413
that I consider most important.

613
01:43:31,414 --> 01:43:34,374
So if someone asked who I am,

614
01:43:34,375 --> 01:43:36,169
I'd just tell them
to watch me perform.

615
01:43:40,214 --> 01:43:45,177
Dancing itself
has become my job.

616
01:43:45,178 --> 01:43:48,472
It's the best way to express

617
01:43:48,473 --> 01:43:53,685
what I want to show
from deep inside.

618
01:43:53,686 --> 01:43:56,521
And even though
I haven't spent

619
01:43:56,522 --> 01:43:58,191
a majority
of my life dancing...

620
01:44:09,827 --> 01:44:15,165
I use dance a lot to express
things I can't put into words.

621
01:44:15,166 --> 01:44:18,627
I love getting lost on stage.

622
01:44:18,628 --> 01:44:23,173
When I'm truly immersed,
some moves come out naturally

623
01:44:23,174 --> 01:44:25,176
and they show
the brighter side of me.

624
01:44:28,846 --> 01:44:31,598
As for my art,

625
01:44:31,599 --> 01:44:37,521
it is just another way
of expressing myself.

626
01:44:37,522 --> 01:44:42,025
So the title is,
"Since There's No Nail Art,

627
01:44:42,026 --> 01:44:43,987
I Used Stickers and Glue."

628
01:44:45,989 --> 01:44:49,199
But dance is what made me
who I am today,

629
01:44:49,200 --> 01:44:50,450
so it means a lot to me.

630
01:44:50,451 --> 01:44:53,705
It's how I express
my inner self.

631
01:44:54,789 --> 01:44:57,249
Now, RedLightz.

632
01:44:57,250 --> 01:45:00,043
Oh, yes.

633
01:45:00,044 --> 01:45:05,340
Our unit's new stage
is coming up.

634
01:45:05,341 --> 01:45:07,342
- "ESCAPE."
- [in English] Yes.

635
01:45:07,343 --> 01:45:09,594
[in Korean]
We're preparing for it.

636
01:45:09,595 --> 01:45:11,889
- We're going to rehearse.
- [in English] Yep.

637
01:45:14,142 --> 01:45:16,310
[choreographer speaks Korean]

638
01:45:22,608 --> 01:45:26,403
Hyunjin: I'm sure everyone has

639
01:45:26,404 --> 01:45:32,284
at least one bruise
or loneliness

640
01:45:32,285 --> 01:45:35,996
that they don't want
to show others.

641
01:45:35,997 --> 01:45:39,750
And in this world, hiding that
feels like the norm.

642
01:45:39,751 --> 01:45:46,132
I also have bruises and worries
I want to hide.

643
01:45:47,925 --> 01:45:51,053
My biggest fear is

644
01:45:51,054 --> 01:45:53,764
that those insecurities
will get exposed to the public.

645
01:45:53,765 --> 01:45:59,519
I'm scared of being caught
showing that part of me.

646
01:45:59,520 --> 01:46:02,731
I guess I never really wanted
to be super famous.

647
01:46:02,732 --> 01:46:06,360
I just wanted
to live my life with STAY.

648
01:46:15,745 --> 01:46:18,914
I started to show
my true self to STAY.

649
01:46:18,915 --> 01:46:23,669
And naturally it led
to more people liking us.

650
01:46:27,757 --> 01:46:32,427
"A wounded blade of grass
smells sweeter."

651
01:46:32,428 --> 01:46:36,223
I first heard this phrase
in 2018,

652
01:46:36,224 --> 01:46:38,558
and it still pushes me forward
to this day.

653
01:46:38,559 --> 01:46:40,811
It felt like it came
during a time

654
01:46:40,812 --> 01:46:43,814
when I was trying
to understand myself.

655
01:46:43,815 --> 01:46:47,984
Like it was telling me
to hang in there.

656
01:46:47,985 --> 01:46:52,280
There are people that support
the wounded blade of grass,

657
01:46:52,281 --> 01:46:53,824
and that's the reason I exist.

658
01:46:53,825 --> 01:46:58,870
And through that,
I gained strength to live on.

659
01:46:58,871 --> 01:47:01,289
- [cheering]
- [in English] Yes, sir.

660
01:47:01,290 --> 01:47:05,377
[in Korean] I just want to
enjoy the ride while I'm here.

661
01:47:05,378 --> 01:47:08,004
Because, in the end, it's only
the good memories that remain.

662
01:47:08,005 --> 01:47:11,883
The hard parts
just fade on their own.

663
01:47:11,884 --> 01:47:14,679
[cheering and applause]

664
01:47:16,514 --> 01:47:19,392
[♪ "MEGAVERSE"]

665
01:50:17,278 --> 01:50:19,238
[cheering and applause]

666
01:50:22,742 --> 01:50:25,411
[♪ "MANIAC"]

667
01:50:32,293 --> 01:50:33,586
Let's go!

668
01:52:53,893 --> 01:52:55,144
Let's go!

669
01:53:24,715 --> 01:53:27,760
[cheering and applause]

670
01:53:36,852 --> 01:53:38,895
[♪ "SUPER BOARD"]

671
01:53:38,896 --> 01:53:40,022
Felix: What's up?

672
01:53:42,525 --> 01:53:44,901
- What's up?
- What's up?

673
01:53:44,902 --> 01:53:45,694
Ow!

674
01:56:38,409 --> 01:56:39,742
Felix: Let's go!

675
01:56:39,743 --> 01:56:42,412
[cheering and applause]

676
01:56:42,413 --> 01:56:45,289
- Okay. I like it.
- Oh, yes.

677
01:56:45,290 --> 01:56:46,499
I like it, sir.

678
01:56:46,500 --> 01:56:47,709
What's up?

679
01:56:47,710 --> 01:56:50,587
[♪ "I Like It"]

680
01:59:08,225 --> 01:59:10,978
- [cheering and applause]
- Felix: What's up, LA?

681
01:59:14,565 --> 01:59:16,148
- Let's sing. Let's go!
- Let's go!

682
01:59:16,149 --> 01:59:19,361
[♪ "My Pace"]

683
01:59:20,946 --> 01:59:22,114
Everybody, sing!

684
01:59:26,827 --> 01:59:28,287
Sing it louder!

685
02:00:22,925 --> 02:00:24,176
You ready? Let's go!

686
02:01:11,014 --> 02:01:12,516
Put your hands up!

687
02:01:49,761 --> 02:01:51,054
Put your hands up!

688
02:02:03,567 --> 02:02:05,193
You ready? Let's go!

689
02:02:17,289 --> 02:02:20,624
- Let's go, yeah.
- [cheering and applause]

690
02:02:20,625 --> 02:02:22,043
We're all champions, huh?

691
02:02:22,044 --> 02:02:24,754
[♪ "BLIND SPOT"]

692
02:02:24,755 --> 02:02:26,506
Hands up if you're a champion!

693
02:02:30,469 --> 02:02:31,261
Let's go!

694
02:03:39,121 --> 02:03:40,372
Let's go.

695
02:04:56,698 --> 02:04:58,533
You ready, LA?

696
02:05:38,615 --> 02:05:41,493
[cheering and applause]

697
02:05:47,749 --> 02:05:50,584
Bang Chan: For some reason,
I don't have an off button.

698
02:05:50,585 --> 02:05:52,127
I'm always on.

699
02:05:52,128 --> 02:05:54,713
Whether it's music or
whether it's, you know,

700
02:05:54,714 --> 02:05:57,800
the awareness
of the other members.

701
02:05:57,801 --> 02:05:59,511
Yeah, I'm always on.

702
02:06:03,723 --> 02:06:06,351
[speaking Korean]

703
02:06:07,894 --> 02:06:09,145
- [in English] You all right?
- Yeah.

704
02:06:11,481 --> 02:06:13,274
[in Korean] Bang Chan is here.

705
02:06:13,275 --> 02:06:18,195
[in English] And I am known
as the leader of Stray Kids.

706
02:06:18,196 --> 02:06:20,656
[in Korean]
Thank you, Bang Chan,

707
02:06:20,657 --> 02:06:23,033
for always
leading the team well.

708
02:06:23,034 --> 02:06:24,994
I didn't really do much.

709
02:06:24,995 --> 02:06:28,747
[in English] But I think out of
all the roles I have to do,

710
02:06:28,748 --> 02:06:31,583
the main role would be
taking care of the kids,

711
02:06:31,584 --> 02:06:35,587
and also to be in charge
of most of our music.

712
02:06:35,588 --> 02:06:38,048
Man [in Korean]:
Hey, Bang Chan, my king!

713
02:06:38,049 --> 02:06:40,384
- You are the king of SKZ world.
- Am I the king?

714
02:06:40,385 --> 02:06:42,094
Director [in English]:
Do you feel pressure

715
02:06:42,095 --> 02:06:44,556
to always be strong
for the others?

716
02:06:45,724 --> 02:06:47,851
Yes. [laughs]

717
02:06:54,065 --> 02:06:58,902
Go! Go, go, go, go, go.
Go, go, go, go.

718
02:06:58,903 --> 02:07:02,239
I mean, I feel pressure
in a lot of things.

719
02:07:02,240 --> 02:07:06,994
Because I need to be the one
that, you know, represents.

720
02:07:06,995 --> 02:07:09,581
The pressure hits hard
all the time.

721
02:07:12,000 --> 02:07:14,376
Which is probably why
I'm always on.

722
02:07:14,377 --> 02:07:17,589
[♪ "ESCAPE"]

723
02:07:24,679 --> 02:07:26,513
I'll be honest,
there's been a lot of times

724
02:07:26,514 --> 02:07:32,019
where I would, uh... explode,

725
02:07:32,020 --> 02:07:36,065
because I'm like the type
to hold in

726
02:07:36,066 --> 02:07:39,818
everything that's going on,
whether it's work,

727
02:07:39,819 --> 02:07:42,197
or the members,
or just personal stuff.

728
02:07:43,865 --> 02:07:45,824
I try my best to hold it in,

729
02:07:45,825 --> 02:07:48,619
but without even me knowing,
that would, like, explode

730
02:07:48,620 --> 02:07:52,123
and then everyone be like, okay,
something happened to him.

731
02:08:04,636 --> 02:08:06,970
Luckily, I have the members

732
02:08:06,971 --> 02:08:08,848
that really help me
get through those times.

733
02:08:11,267 --> 02:08:13,019
[speaking Korean]

734
02:08:14,938 --> 02:08:17,689
Bang Chan [in English]:
Thinking too much might be

735
02:08:17,690 --> 02:08:20,234
one of my biggest insecurities.

736
02:08:20,235 --> 02:08:24,154
I know that that's a fact,
but I keep doing it.

737
02:08:24,155 --> 02:08:27,408
I'm a hider, not a show-er.

738
02:08:27,409 --> 02:08:31,370
I think these days
people have been able to see

739
02:08:31,371 --> 02:08:36,458
my more vulnerable sides,
especially the members.

740
02:08:36,459 --> 02:08:39,420
I've been showing them
how I really feel.

741
02:08:39,421 --> 02:08:42,131
I've been very, very honest
with them.

742
02:08:42,132 --> 02:08:44,425
[in Korean] STAY,
shall I tell you a good TMI?

743
02:08:44,426 --> 02:08:45,759
After the song ended.

744
02:08:45,760 --> 02:08:49,638
- [gasping]
- [fans laughing]

745
02:08:49,639 --> 02:08:51,306
Bang Chan [in English]:
Before now,

746
02:08:51,307 --> 02:08:53,183
I would still try to hide it
from the members

747
02:08:53,184 --> 02:08:56,603
because I wanted to be
that strong, dependent leader

748
02:08:56,604 --> 02:08:58,189
that I should be.

749
02:09:02,902 --> 02:09:04,987
If I'm gonna be
the leader of Stray Kids,

750
02:09:04,988 --> 02:09:08,574
might as well be
the leader of STAY as well.

751
02:09:08,575 --> 02:09:11,869
They could be like, huh,
that's our leader, you know.

752
02:09:11,870 --> 02:09:13,121
He's here
to protect us.

753
02:09:17,750 --> 02:09:20,919
I think one of
the most memorable sentences

754
02:09:20,920 --> 02:09:24,882
that STAYs would tell me that
I remember the most would be,

755
02:09:24,883 --> 02:09:27,134
"Your music saved my life."

756
02:09:27,135 --> 02:09:30,888
I'm really grateful
that I could help out

757
02:09:30,889 --> 02:09:34,224
people in need through music.

758
